cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of a novel counter architecture for per-flow measurements on high-speed links. It applies the concept of spatial coupling to improve the performance of the original architecture and analyzes its asymptotic performance. This falls under the scope of Information Theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with per-flow measurements on high-speed links, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel counter architecture and analyzes its performance, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with per-flow measurements on high-speed links, which can be seen as a type of network. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the complexity of decoding the proposed counter architecture and its spatially-coupled version, which falls under the scope of Computational Complexity.
